  "description": "For the first official episode, I am pleased to interview my former command team partner on Op Sculpture: LCol Mike Vernon of the PPCLI and the Calgary Highlanders. In this episode, LCol Vernon describes his deployment to Afghanistan and the production of his documentary Desert Lions.  Listen as he discuses how he became an officer in the CF and the mentors and influences in his life. This is a podcast worth listening to. You can support this site by shopping [&#8230;]",
  "content:encoded": "<p>For the first official episode, I am pleased to interview my former command team partner on <a title=\"Op Sculpture\" href=\"http://www.forces.gc.ca/en/operations-abroad-current/op-sculpture.page\" target=\"_blank\">Op Sculpture</a>:<a title=\"The Calgary Highlanders Commanding Officers\" href=\"http://www.calgaryhighlanders.com/appointments/commanders.htm\" target=\"_blank\"> LCol Mike Vernon</a> of the <a title=\"PPCLI Home Page\" href=\"htthttp://www.ppcli.com\" target=\"_blank\">PPCLI</a> and the<a title=\"The Calgary Highlanders\" href=\"http://www.calgaryhighlanders.com/\" target=\"_blank\"> Calgary Highlanders</a>.</p>\n<p>In this episode, LCol Vernon describes his deployment to <a title=\"Canadian Mission in Afghanistan\" href=\"http://www.afghanistan.gc.ca/canada-afghanistan/index.aspxhttp://\" target=\"_blank\">Afghanistan</a> and the <a title=\"Lone Wolf Communications\" href=\"http://lonewolfcommunications.wordpress.com/about-2/mike-vernon/\" target=\"_blank\">production</a> of his documentary <a title=\"Desert Lions\" href=\"http://lonewolfcommunications.wordpress.com/afghanistan-2010/desert-lions-canadian-forces-mentors-in-afghanistan/\" target=\"_blank\">Desert Lions</a>.  Listen as he discuses how he became an officer in the CF and the mentors and influences in his life. This is a podcast worth listening to.</p>\n<p>You can support this site by shopping on <a title=\"Amazon.ca\" href=\"http://www.amazon.ca?_encoding=UTF8&tag=thecanamilihi-20\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon</a>.  You still enjoy Amazon&#8217;s great prices, but a portion of your purchase goes to supporting the show.</p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-34-71\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/LCol-Mike-Vernon20130918.mp3?_=71\" /><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/LCol-Mike-Vernon20130918.mp3\">http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/LCol-Mike-Vernon20130918.mp3</a></audio>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/DSCF0504.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft\" alt=\"DSCF0504\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/DSCF0504-300x225.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/P7290193.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-77 alignright\" alt=\"OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/P7290193-224x300.jpg\" width=\"251\" height=\"337\" /></a><a class=\"alignleft\" href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/197.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignright\" alt=\"197\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/197-300x225.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/clasp.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-81 alignright\" alt=\"clasp\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/clasp-200x300.jpg\" width=\"278\" height=\"416\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/clasp-200x300.jpg 200w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/clasp.jpg 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 278px) 100vw, 278px\" /></a><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/246.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"246\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/246-225x300.jpg\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\n<p>Honourary Paramount Chief Mike Vernon</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/cgy-mike-vernon-20121204-new.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-82 alignleft\" alt=\"cgy-mike-vernon-20121204-new\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/cgy-mike-vernon-20121204-new-300x168.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"168\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/cgy-mike-vernon-20121204-new-300x168.jpg 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/cgy-mike-vernon-20121204-new.jpg 620w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/sierraleone4.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"sierraleone4\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/sierraleone4-300x203.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"203\" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/CMHP-Logo600x600.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-29\" alt=\"CMHP Logo600x600\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/CMHP-Logo600x600-300x300.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/CMHP-Logo600x600-300x300.png 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/CMHP-Logo600x600-150x150.png 150w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/CMHP-Logo600x600-200x200.png 200w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/CMHP-Logo600x600.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n",
